This paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it investigates the use of common libraries in Android apps, which is a software engineering concern. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it mentions piggybacking detection and malware detection, which are security concerns. Additionally, it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category as it discusses the packaging model of Android apps and the code necessary for their execution. It may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category as it analyzes a dataset of 1.5 million apps from Google Play. Finally, it may belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it discusses the proportion of Android app code contributed by common libraries.
